  "time_ut": 1657974269,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0b95\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1 \u0b87\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0bc1\u0bb5 \u0b89\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Military assistance to clear the ranks",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Power and Energy Minister Kanchana Wijesekara has said that in order to implement the National Fuel Permit Card, those who are currently in the fuel queue should be removed, and has sought military assistance for the same.",
        "In a press conference held today, he informed the above matter and said that those who are currently in the fuel queue should immediately register for the fuel permit on the website.",
        "The minister also said that the security forces would assist in removing the queuers from the fuel station queues as they would not be able to distinguish between the queuers and the new registrants.",
        "He pointed out that petrol stations of the Sri Lanka Petroleum Corporation will no longer operate only under fuel permits and no fuel will be available if you stand in a queue.",
        "He said that until the implementation of the fuel permit, the Lanka IOC company's filling stations will operate as usual and thereafter the entire country will follow the same pattern.",
        "The Minister further informed that if a particular individual or company owns more than one vehicle, each vehicle may have a separate driver and one vehicle can be registered only under one National Identity Card.",
        "Meanwhile, it is noted that the website http://fuelpass.gov.lk/ provided for registration of information is currently down."
      ],
